B.T4=new A.c("The catecholaminergic hypothesis of TBI recovery identifies which three neurotransmitter systems as critical for neural repair?","Dopaminergic, noradrenergic, and cholinergic.")
B.NJ=new A.c("Why do medications reach higher CNS concentrations in an injured brain compared to a healthy one?","Altered blood-brain barrier permeability.")
B.Tw=new A.c("What is the cardinal pharmacological rule for treating patients with TBI?",'"Start low, go slow."')
B.RQ=new A.c("Why is haloperidol specifically avoided in early TBI recovery?","It blocks dopaminergic pathways essential for neuroplasticity and prolongs Post-Traumatic Amnesia (PTA).")
B.TL=new A.c("Mechanism: Haloperidol","D2 dopamine receptor antagonist.")
B.Y9=new A.c("What is the maximum recommended duration for phenytoin use as post-traumatic seizure (PTS) prophylaxis in the absence of documented seizures?","7 days.")
B.WJ=new A.c("Which medication is currently preferred over phenytoin for early PTS prophylaxis due to a better cognitive profile?","Levetiracetam.")
B.UD=new A.c("Chronic use of phenytoin is avoided in TBI because it impairs motor recovery and _____.","Cognition (specifically attention, processing speed, and memory).")
