B.UB=new A.c("Phenobarbital increases the _____ of GABA-A receptor chloride channel opening.","Duration.")
B.RW=new A.c("Why are benzodiazepines avoided for treating agitation in TBI patients?","They cause excessive sedation and can trigger paradoxical agitation.")
B.Q2=new A.c("What is the impact of anticholinergic medications on the TBI-injured brain?","They worsen already impaired memory, learning, and attention.")
B.WI=new A.c("Which common antiemetic should be avoided in TBI because it acts as a D2 antagonist?","Metoclopramide (Reglan).")
B.Qe=new A.c("What is the preferred alternative antiemetic in TBI that does not block dopamine receptors?","Ondansetron.")
B.SP=new A.c("Amantadine is the only medication with Level B evidence for accelerating functional recovery in which condition?","Disorders of Consciousness (DOC).")
B.Vb=new A.c("Mechanism: Amantadine (Dopaminergic)","Enhances presynaptic dopamine release.")
B.R7=new A.c("Amantadine acts as a weak antagonist at which excitatory receptor?","NMDA receptor.")
B.UM=new A.c("To prevent insomnia, the second daily dose of amantadine should be administered no later than _____.","Noon.")
B.ZK=new A.c("What skin condition is a known side effect of amantadine use?","Livedo reticularis.")
B.VU=new A.c("Mechanism: Methylphenidate","Blocks dopamine (DAT) and norepinephrine (NET) transporter reuptake.")
B.MW=new A.c("What is the primary clinical indication for using methylphenidate after TBI?","Attention deficits and processing speed impairment.")
B.Ym=new A.c("Mechanism: Bromocriptine","Direct D2 dopamine receptor agonist.")
B.W7=new A.c("Bromocriptine is the agent of choice for treating which frontal lobe-mediated condition?","Akinetic mutism (or apathy/abulia).")
B.Xa=new A.c("What is a significant side effect to monitor during the first dose of bromocriptine?","Hypotension.")
B.Oh=new A.c("Which class of medication is preferred for wakefulness in TBI when attention is NOT the primary deficit?","Modafinil or Armodafinil.")
B.Zp=new A.c("Donepezil improves memory in TBI by inhibiting which enzyme?","Acetylcholinesterase.")
B.Y8=new A.c("Which medication is the first choice for treating insomnia in TBI because it is non-habit forming and does not impair cognition?","Trazodone.")
B.Qv=new A.c("Why is diphenhydramine (Benadryl) avoided for sleep in TBI patients?","Its anticholinergic effects worsen cognitive impairment.")
B.U3=new A.c("What is the most common psychiatric complication following a TBI?","Depression.")
B.X9=new A.c("Which class of antidepressants is considered first-line for TBI due to having the fewest drug interactions?","SSRIs (e.g., Sertraline, Citalopram).")
B.NQ=new A.c("Why is bupropion generally avoided in patients with a history of TBI?","It lowers the seizure threshold.")
B.V5=new A.c("Differentiate the mood in Depression vs. Apathy.","Depression involves sadness/guilt; Apathy involves indifference/flatness without sadness.")
B.VV=new A.c("Which medication class is first-line for treating apathy, whereas it may be ineffective for depression?","Dopaminergic agents (e.g., Methylphenidate).")
B.WW=new A.c("According to the pharmacological hierarchy, what is the first-line drug class for TBI-related agitation?","Beta-blockers (e.g., propranolol).")
B.Ot=new A.c("What are the primary contraindications for using propranolol for agitation?","Asthma and heart block.")
B.Wi=new A.c("Which anticonvulsant is a strong CYP450 inducer and requires therapeutic drug monitoring?","Phenytoin.")
B.UV=new A.c("Which anticonvulsant is associated with a risk of hyponatremia due to SIADH?","Carbamazepine.")
B.TT=new A.c("Valproic acid can double the serum levels of which medication, increasing the risk of Stevens-Johnson Syndrome?","Lamotrigine.")
B.OE=new A.c("Mechanism: Oral Baclofen","GABA-B receptor agonist.")
B.U1=new A.c("What is the primary benefit of Intrathecal Baclofen (ITB) over oral baclofen?","It bypasses the blood-brain barrier, reducing systemic side effects like sedation.")
B.T6=new A.c("What is the gold standard treatment for focal spasticity in TBI?","Botulinum Toxin (BoNT-A) injections.")
B.NU=new A.c("Which oral antispasmodic acts peripherally on the sarcoplasmic reticulum and is less likely to cause cognitive sedation?","Dantrolene.")
B.Q1=new A.c("What is the potentially fatal risk associated with Intrathecal Baclofen pump failure?","Baclofen withdrawal syndrome.")
B.Pv=new A.c("What was the outcome of Phase III clinical trials (PROTECT III and SyNAPSe) for progesterone in TBI?","They failed to show clinical efficacy.")
B.PA=new A.c('In TBI pharmacology, what does the mnemonic "P pushes enzymes up" refer to?',"Phenytoin is a strong CYP450 inducer.")
B.WS=new A.c("Which medication should be used for agitation if sleep disruption is also a contributing factor?","Trazodone.")
B.VK=new A.c("What is the most significant predictor of neurobehavioral symptom distress in TBI survivors?","CNS polypharmacy.")
B.OP=new A.c("Concept: Livedo reticularis","Definition: A purplish, lace-like skin discoloration often seen as a side effect of Amantadine.")
B.YX=new A.c("Why is levetiracetam generally preferred over phenytoin for patients with multiple comorbidities?","It has no significant CYP450 drug interactions.")
B.VD=new A.c("Which neurotransmitter system is primarily targeted by donepezil to treat memory deficits?","Cholinergic system.")
B.Q9=new A.c("True or False: SSRIs may worsen symptoms of apathy in TBI patients.","True (by dampening emotional reactivity).")
B.Q4=new A.c("What is the indicated dose of amantadine for reducing irritability in TBI?","100 mg BID.")
B.Te=new A.c("Mechanism: Tizanidine","Alpha-2 adrenergic agonist.")
B.Tf=new A.c("Which anticonvulsant undergoes auto-induction, meaning it induces its own metabolism over time?","Carbamazepine.")
B.ZA=new A.c("For which medication is Stevens-Johnson Syndrome a rare but serious side effect, particularly in pediatric patients treated for wakefulness?","Modafinil.")
B.VC=new A.c("A patient with TBI presents with emotional flatness and lack of concern but no sadness. What is the likely diagnosis?","Apathy.")
B.a_f=new A.c("Which medication is an ergot-derived dopamine agonist used for akinetic mutism?","Bromocriptine.")
B.Pp=new A.c('Why is the use of typical antipsychotics like haloperidol described as a "Board Pearl" for avoidance?',"They block the very dopaminergic tracts needed for recovery and functional repair.")
B.Z3=new A.c("What is the specific GABA receptor targeted by Baclofen?","GABAB.")
B.a_l=new A.c("How does the clearance of levetiracetam differ from phenytoin?","Levetiracetam is renally cleared; phenytoin is hepatically cleared.")
