B.a8B=s(["Translational (linear) acceleration","Rotational (angular) acceleration","Direct contact forces","Static loading"],t.s)
B.agm=new A.O("Which specific mechanism of primary brain injury is recognized as the most damaging force, responsible for shearing axons at the gray-white matter junctions?",B.a8B,1,"Rotational forces create the greatest shear stress across tissues of different densities, leading to widespread axonal disruption.","pathophysiology")
B.a7y=s(["Occipital poles","Parietal lobes","Orbitofrontal cortex","Posterior temporal lobe"],t.s)
B.ahO=new A.O("A patient presents with personality changes and impaired social judgment following a TBI. Based on the common locations of contusions, which area was likely injured?",B.a7y,2,"Contusions in the inferior frontal region are common due to the rough bony surface of the anterior cranial fossa and lead to disinhibition.","pathophysiology")
B.a7k=s(["Biconvex shape that does not cross suture lines","Crescent-shaped blood that crosses suture lines","A 'lucid interval' following the initial impact","Involvement of the middle meningeal artery"],t.s)
B.ag6=new A.O("Which CT finding and clinical characteristic are most indicative of a Subdural Hematoma (SDH) rather than an Epidural Hematoma (EDH)?",B.a7k,1,"Subdural hematomas occur in the space between the dura and arachnoid, allowing blood to spread along the hemisphere's curvature across sutures.","pathophysiology")
B.a6j=s(["Dorsolateral midbrain","Parasagittal gray-white junction only","Corpus callosum","Internal capsule and basal ganglia"],t.s)
B.afu=new A.O("According to the Adams Grading System for Diffuse Axonal Injury (DAI), what is the anatomical location involved in a Grade 2 injury?",B.a6j,2,"Grade 2 DAI involves the white matter at the gray-white junction plus focal lesions in the corpus callosum, often the splenium.","pathophysiology")
B.a9x=s(["Glutamate inhibition leads to a shutdown of glucose transport","Massive calcium efflux causes the mitochondria to stop producing ATP","Glucose demand for ionic pumps exceeds the available supply","The brain switches entirely to lipid metabolism due to insulin resistance"],t.s)
B.ahv=new A.O("In the neurometabolic cascade of concussion described by Giza and Hovda, why does the brain enter a 'metabolic crisis' or energy mismatch?",B.a9x,2,"The Na+/K+ ATPase pumps work overtime to correct the ionic flux, creating a massive demand for glucose that outstrips supply.","pathophysiology")
B.a5I=s(["Vasogenic edema","Interstitial edema","Cytotoxic edema","Hydrostatic edema"],t.s)
B.ahi=new A.O("Which form of cerebral edema is typically seen after severe TBI and is noted for being unresponsive to steroid treatment?",B.a5I,2,"Cytotoxic edema is intracellular swelling caused by ionic pump failure; steroids are contraindicated as they do not help and may increase mortality.","pathophysiology")
B.a9D=s(["Caspase-dependent DNA fragmentation","Iron-dependent lipid peroxidation","Cellular swelling and membrane rupture due to energy failure","Excessive mitochondrial fusion"],t.s)
B.ai4=new A.O("Ferroptosis is an emerging board-relevant concept describing a specific pathway of cell death in TBI. What is its defining characteristic?",B.a9D,1,"Ferroptosis is driven by the accumulation of iron which catalyzes the lethal peroxidation of lipids within the cell membrane.","pathophysiology")
B.a5k=s(["Sleep allows the blood-brain barrier to fully close for the first time","Glymphatic clearance of metabolic waste increases by 60% during sleep","Sleep inhibits the M1 pro-inflammatory phenotype of microglia","Dreaming activates the internal capsule to prevent motor deficits"],t.s)
B.agE=new A.O("Based on research into the glymphatic system, why is sleep hygiene considered critical for neuroprotection after a brain injury?",B.a5k,1,"The glymphatic system, which flushes interstitial waste like tau and amyloid-beta, is significantly more active during sleep compared to wakefulness.","pathophysiology")
B.a5_=s(["CTE tau is found primarily in the medial temporal lobe","CTE tau is distributed at the depths of cortical sulci in a perivascular pattern","AD tau is localized to the superior cerebellar peduncle","CTE tau is found only in the white matter tracts"],t.s)
B.ain=new A.O("How does the chronic tau pathology found in Chronic Traumatic Encephalopathy (CTE) differ anatomically from that seen in Alzheimer's Disease (AD)?",B.a5_,1,"CTE is distinguished by tau accumulation at the sulcal depths and around small blood vessels, particularly in the superficial cortical layers.","pathophysiology")
B.a6V=s(["< 110 mmHg; it increases the risk of seizure","< 90 mmHg; it doubles the mortality rate","< 70 mmHg; it causes immediate brain death","< 100 mmHg; it leads to vasogenic edema"],t.s)
B.ahc=new A.O("A patient experiences a single episode of systemic hypotension with a systolic blood pressure (SBP) below a critical threshold. What is this threshold, and what is its clinical significance in TBI?",B.a6V,1,"A single episode of SBP < 90 mmHg is strongly associated with doubled mortality due to the loss of cerebral autoregulation and resulting ischemia.","pathophysiology")
B.a5M=s(["Rapid waves of hyperpolarization that reduce metabolic demand","Waves of neuronal depolarization that propagate across the cortex","An immediate electrical silence that prevents secondary injury","A phenomenon only detectable by invasive brain tissue oxygen monitors"],t.s)
B.aih=new A.O("Cortical spreading depolarization (CSD) occurs in a significant percentage of surgical TBI patients. How is this phenomenon characterized?",B.a5M,1,"CSD is characterized by waves of near-complete depolarization that spread at 2-5 mm/min, worsening secondary injury.","pathophysiology")
B.a94=s(["M1 dominance occurs within the first 3 hours","M1 phenotype begins to dominate around day 7 and persists","The M1 phenotype disappears entirely by week 2","M1 and M2 phenotypes reach a permanent equilibrium at 24 hours"],t.s)
B.ahR=new A.O("What is the typical timeline for microglial activation following TBI, specifically regarding when the pro-inflammatory (M1) phenotype begins to dominate?",B.a94,1,"After an initial reparative (M2) phase that peaks around days 3-5, the pro-inflammatory M1 phenotype takes over by day 7.","pathophysiology")
B.a9z=s(["The skull expands slightly to accommodate the volume before snapping back","Once compensatory mechanisms are exhausted, compliance drops","Arterial blood pressure increases to match the volume expansion","The brain tissue becomes more compressible over time"],t.s)
B.afU=new A.O("According to the Monro-Kellie doctrine, why does intracranial pressure (ICP) rise exponentially rather than linearly as a mass expands?",B.a9z,1,"Once the displacement of CSF and venous blood is maximized, any further volume increase leads to rapid, exponential pressure spikes.","pathophysiology")
B.a5m=s(["Myelin debris triggers the immediate release of iron leading to ferroptosis","It acts as a physical barrier that prevents astrocytes from forming scars","Myelin-associated inhibitors signal through the NgR1 receptor to suppress regeneration","It causes the massive efflux of potassium from the extracellular space"],t.s)
B.agu=new A.O("What is the primary mechanism by which myelin debris from injured axons hinders recovery in Diffuse Axonal Injury (DAI)?",B.a5m,2,"Molecules like Nogo-A and MAG in the debris signal to axons to stop growing and inhibit the differentiation of oligodendrocyte progenitor cells.","pathophysiology")
B.a72=s(["Non-contrast CT head","T2-weighted MRI","Diffusion Tensor Imaging (DTI)","Cerebral Angiography"],t.s)
B.afd=new A.O("Which imaging modality is considered the most sensitive for detecting subtle Diffuse Axonal Injury (DAI) that might be missed on conventional MRI?",B.a72,2,"DTI measures fractional anisotropy, which reflects the integrity of white matter tracts and can detect subtle damage.","pathophysiology")
B.a8D=s([B.agm,B.ahO,B.ag6,B.afu,B.ahv,B.ahi,B.ai4,B.agE,B.ain,B.ahc,B.aih,B.ahR,B.afU,B.agu,B.afd],t.e)
B.qO=s([],t.Xn)
B.auV=new A.lb("Mechanical Impact",B.lA,"Primary injury: shearing forces tear axons, contusion of cortical tissue, and vascular disruption causes hemorrhage. This damage is immediate and irreversible at the moment of impact.",B.qO)
B.avK=new A.k9("Magnesium Sulfate","NMDA receptor blockade limits Ca2+ influx","Ionic flux phase")
B.a9k=s([B.avK],t.Xn)
B.auZ=new A.lb("Ionic Flux",B.q1,"Massive neuronal depolarization triggers K+ efflux and Na+/Ca2+ influx through mechanically disrupted channels. Indiscriminate neurotransmitter release overwhelms synaptic machinery.",B.a9k)
B.avL=new A.k9("Amantadine","Weak NMDA antagonist; reduces excitotoxic signaling","Glutamate cascade")
B.a5A=s([B.avL],t.Xn)
B.auY=new A.lb("Glutamate Excitotoxicity",B.io,"Excessive glutamate activates NMDA and AMPA receptors, causing unregulated Ca2+ influx. Sustained depolarization spreads injury to previously uninjured neurons in the penumbra.",B.a5A)
B.a0v=new A.aw(62893,"MaterialIcons",!1)
B.avN=new A.k9("Osmotic Therapy","Mannitol / hypertonic saline reduces cerebral edema and ICP","Cellular swelling from ATP failure")
B.a4B=s([B.avN],t.Xn)
B.auW=new A.lb("Mitochondrial Failure",B.a0v,"Intracellular Ca2+ overload damages mitochondrial membranes. ATP production collapses, Na+/K+-ATPase fails, and oxidative stress accelerates. The cell enters an energy crisis.",B.a4B)
B.a14=new A.aw(983734,"MaterialIcons",!1)
B.avO=new A.k9("Therapeutic Hypothermia","Lowers metabolic rate, reduces ROS generation","Free radical production")
B.avJ=new A.k9("Progesterone (investigational)","Membrane stabilization, reduces oxidative stress","Lipid peroxidation")
B.a79=s([B.avO,B.avJ],t.Xn)
B.auU=new A.lb("Free Radical Damage",B.a14,"Reactive oxygen species (ROS) attack cell membranes via lipid peroxidation, damage DNA strands, and denature proteins. The antioxidant defense system is overwhelmed.",B.a79)
B.avM=new A.k9("Decompressive Craniectomy","Removes bone flap to allow brain expansion, lowers ICP","Refractory cerebral edema")
B.a4H=s([B.avM],t.Xn)
B.auX=new A.lb("Neuroinflammation",B.q5,"Microglial activation (M1 pro-inflammatory phenotype) releases cytokines (TNF-alpha, IL-1beta, IL-6). Blood-brain barrier breakdown causes vasogenic edema. Cytokine storm propagates injury.",B.a4H)
B.a0B=new A.aw(63115,"MaterialIcons",!1)
B.av_=new A.lb("Cell Death",B.a0B,"Apoptosis (programmed cell death via caspase activation) and necrosis converge. Wallerian degeneration of damaged axons. Initiates chronic neurodegeneration pathway (tau, TDP-43).",B.qO)
B.a8E=s([B.auV,B.auZ,B.auY,B.auW,B.auU,B.auX,B.av_],A.aa("q<lb>"))
B.To=new A.c("According to the Brain Trauma Foundation (BTF) 4th Edition, identify the only Level I recommendation.","Steroids are contraindicated for the treatment of traumatic brain injury.")
B.NO=new A.c("Which landmark clinical trial demonstrated that methylprednisolone increases mortality in patients with TBI?","The CRASH trial.")
B.Vu=new A.c("The current Brain Trauma Foundation guideline (4th Ed) defines the threshold for treating intracranial pressure (ICP) at _____.","> 22 mmHg")
B.Oe=new A.c("What clinical criteria, in addition to a normal CT scan, indicate ICP monitoring in severe TBI patients?","At least two of: age > 40, motor posturing, or SBP < 90 mmHg.")
B.MH=new A.c("Term: External Ventricular Drain (EVD)","Definition: The gold standard for ICP monitoring that also allows for therapeutic CSF drainage.")
B.ZF=new A.c("At what anatomical landmark must an external ventricular drain (EVD) be calibrated?","The foramen of Monro, which corresponds to the tragus of the ear.")
B.Q7=new A.c("Which trial found no significant difference in 6-month mortality between ICP monitor-based management and imaging-based management?","The BEST-TRIP trial.")
B.WL=new A.c("The standard target range for Cerebral Perfusion Pressure (CPP) in TBI patients is _____.","60-70 mmHg")
B.WV=new A.c("What systemic complication is associated with aggressively pushing CPP > 70 mmHg using vasopressors?","Adult Respiratory Distress Syndrome (ARDS).")
B.Y_=new A.c("Cerebral ischemia and increased morbidity are likely to occur when the CPP falls below _____.","50 mmHg")
B.Yz=new A.c("Why is mannitol specifically contraindicated in hypotensive TBI patients?","It is an osmotic diuretic that causes volume depletion, potentially worsening hypotension.")
B.VH=new A.c("When administering hypertonic saline (HTS) for ICP management, serum sodium should be monitored to stay below _____.","160 mEq/L")
B.a_7=new A.c("The serum osmolality limit for administering mannitol is _____.","< 320 mOsm/L")
B.P2=new A.c("Phenytoin is recommended for seizure prophylaxis in TBI for only the first _____ days post-injury.","7")
B.W2=new A.c("Which anti-epileptic drug is often preferred over phenytoin due to its lack of drug-level monitoring and fewer cognitive side effects?","Levetiracetam (Keppra).")
B.PR=new A.c("In the SIBICC tiered algorithm, identify one Tier 1 intervention for ICP management.","Head of bed elevation to 30 degrees.")
B.MV=new A.c("In the SIBICC tiered algorithm, neuromuscular blockade (e.g., cisatracurium) is classified as a _____ intervention.","Tier 2")
B.Xw=new A.c("Identify the primary mechanism by which hyperventilation acutely reduces intracranial pressure.","Induced cerebral vasoconstriction due to decreased PaCO2.")
B.NM=new A.c("Hyperventilation should be avoided during the first 24 hours after injury because _____ is already naturally reduced.","Cerebral blood flow (CBF)")
B.XI=new A.c("For a patient aged 15-49, the BTF Level III recommendation for Systolic Blood Pressure (SBP) is _____.",">= 110 mmHg")
B.P5=new A.c("For a patient aged 50-69, the BTF Level III recommendation for Systolic Blood Pressure (SBP) is _____.",">= 100 mmHg")
B.YA=new A.c("Based on the POLAR and Eurotherm3235 trials, what is the current standard for temperature management in acute TBI?","Controlled normothermia (36.0-37.5 degrees C).")
B.Yw=new A.c("According to the CRASH-3 trial, Tranexamic Acid (TXA) significantly reduces head injury death in which specific TBI severity group?","Mild-to-moderate TBI (GCS 9-15).")
B.WO=new A.c("To be effective for TBI, Tranexamic Acid (TXA) must be administered within _____ hours of injury.","3")
B.Un=new A.c("What did the ProTECT III and SyNAPSe Phase III trials conclude about progesterone in severe TBI?","Progesterone has no benefit in severe TBI, despite promising preclinical and Phase II data.")
B.Qd=new A.c("Why does the brain have a unique susceptibility to consumptive coagulopathy after injury?","The brain contains the highest concentration of tissue factor of any organ.")
B.Yx=new A.c("Term: GFAP (Glial Fibrillary Acidic Protein)","Definition: An FDA-cleared blood biomarker for astrocyte injury used to triage mild TBI.")
B.Ya=new A.c("Term: UCH-L1 (Ubiquitin C-terminal Hydrolase L1)","Definition: An FDA-cleared blood biomarker indicating neuronal degradation.")
B.Na=new A.c("What was the primary conclusion of the DECRA trial regarding early bifrontal decompressive craniectomy for diffuse injury?","It decreased ICP but was associated with worse functional outcomes (GOS-E).")
B.Xt=new A.c("How did the RESCUEicp trial differ from the DECRA trial regarding the timing of decompressive craniectomy?","RESCUEicp studied craniectomy as a last-resort rescue therapy for refractory ICP.")
B.T0=new A.c("To prevent further herniation during a decompressive craniectomy, the bone flap should be at least _____.","12 x 15 cm")
B.US=new A.c("Which herniation syndrome is characterized by an ipsilateral CN III palsy and contralateral hemiparesis?","Uncal (Transtentorial) herniation.")
B.Oa=new A.c("What is the clinical significance of a 'Kernohan notch' during uncal herniation?","It is a false localizing sign causing hemiparesis ipsilateral to the primary lesion.")
B.XN=new A.c("Identify the three components of the Cushing Triad.","Hypertension, bradycardia, and irregular respirations.")
B.Zv=new A.c("By which post-injury day does the BTF recommend reaching full nutritional replacement to decrease mortality?","Day 5 to 7.")
B.a_k=new A.c("What is the recommended daily protein intake for a patient with severe TBI?","1.5-2 g/kg/day")
B.Qs=new A.c("When should pharmacologic DVT prophylaxis be initiated in a TBI patient if the follow-up CT is stable?","24-72 hours after stable imaging.")
B.Rq=new A.c("Which advanced monitor measures brain tissue oxygen levels?","PbtO2")
B.Ta=new A.c("What is the treatment threshold for brain tissue oxygen (PbtO2) according to BTF guidelines?","< 15 mmHg")
B.Yo=new A.c("In cerebral microdialysis, a lactate/pyruvate ratio (LPR) greater than _____ indicates a metabolic crisis.","40")
B.QY=new A.c("Which neuromuscular blocking agent is preferred in TBI management because it has organ-independent metabolism (Hofmann elimination)?","Cisatracurium.")
B.TQ=new A.c("The last-resort pharmacologic intervention for refractory ICP before surgical craniectomy is typically _____.","Barbiturate coma (e.g., Pentobarbital).")
B.Vj=new A.c("How do clinicians monitor the depth of a barbiturate-induced coma for ICP control?","EEG monitoring for burst suppression.")
B.XZ=new A.c("What is the primary clinical difference between SIADH and Cerebral Salt Wasting (CSW)?","Cerebral Salt Wasting involves extracellular volume depletion, whereas SIADH is euvolemic.")
B.Zg=new A.c("A patient with a skull fracture near the sella turcica presents with hypernatremia and dilute urine (SG < 1.005). What is the diagnosis?","Diabetes Insipidus (DI).")
B.Ps=new A.c("What is the standard first-line medication for treating central Diabetes Insipidus?","Desmopressin (DDAVP).")
B.Po=new A.c("To avoid osmotic demyelination syndrome, sodium should not be corrected faster than _____ per 24 hours.","<= 10 mEq/L")
B.MK=new A.c("Paroxysmal Sympathetic Hyperactivity (PSH) typically begins how many days after the initial TBI?","5-7 days.")
B.Ts=new A.c("Which two medications have the strongest evidence for managing the autonomic surges of Paroxysmal Sympathetic Hyperactivity (PSH)?","Morphine and Propranolol.")
B.QZ=new A.c("What is the most common type of hydrocephalus following traumatic brain injury?","Communicating hydrocephalus.")
B.PJ=new A.c("Which radiological sign on CT helps distinguish posttraumatic hydrocephalus from atrophy (ex vacuo)?","Temporal horn enlargement and periventricular lucency.")
B.RS=new A.c("Which imaging modality is the gold standard for the acute assessment of TBI and is mandatory for a GCS < 13?","Computed Tomography (CT).")
B.Vw=new A.c("Describe the classic CT appearance of an Epidural Hematoma (EDH).","An elliptical or biconvex-shaped hyperdensity.")
B.Sj=new A.c("Subdural hematomas (SDH) are typically caused by the disruption of _____.","Bridging veins.")
B.WT=new A.c("What is the mortality risk associated with a single episode of hypotension (SBP < 90 mmHg) in severe TBI?","It doubles the mortality rate.")
B.Vr=new A.c("In the SIBICC algorithm, 'controlled normothermia' targets a temperature of _____.","36.0-37.5 degrees C")
B.Zi=new A.c("Cerebral blood flow is most significantly compromised in which herniation syndrome that results in respiratory arrest?","Tonsillar (Cerebellar) herniation.")
B.S2=new A.c("Which herniation syndrome involves the cingulate gyrus moving under the falx cerebri, potentially causing contralateral leg weakness?","Subfalcine (Cingulate) herniation.")
B.QS=new A.c("According to the BTF nutrition guidelines, transgastric jejunal feeding is recommended to reduce the risk of _____.","Ventilator-associated pneumonia (VAP).")
B.Oj=new A.c("What percentage of severe TBI patients experience gastroparesis, often necessitating post-pyloric feeding?","50%")
B.Oc=new A.c("In acute TBI, what is the target fibrinogen level to manage brain-specific coagulopathy?","> 1.5-2.0 g/L")
B.S7=new A.c("Which intracranial monitor cannot be recalibrated after insertion and is prone to measurement drift?","Intraparenchymal monitors (e.g., Codman, Camino).")
B.Vg=new A.c("Identify the risk factor associated with the highest incidence (33-50%) of post-traumatic seizures.","Penetrating brain injury.")
B.a_Q=new A.c("A target PaCO2 of 30-35 mmHg is recommended only as _____ therapy during acute herniation.","Bridge")
B.S_=new A.c("What is the peak timeframe for the hypermetabolic response following a severe TBI?","2 weeks post-injury.")
B.a_C=new A.c("According to the CRASH-3 trial, what was the effect of TXA on patients with severe TBI (GCS 3-8)?","There was no significant benefit.")
B.QW=new A.c("Which diagnostic test is more sensitive than conventional PT/PTT for detecting the 'brain-specific' coagulopathy of TBI?","Viscoelastic testing (TEG or ROTEM).")
B.O0=new A.c("Define the 'syndrome of the trephined'.","Neurological deterioration following a craniectomy that often improves after cranioplasty skull replacement.")
B.S0=new A.c("Which surgical emergency is characterized by a 'lucid interval' followed by rapid deterioration?","Epidural Hematoma (EDH).")
B.Sx=new A.c("For ICP management, the SIBICC algorithm recommends MAP challenges in which tier?","Tier 2")
B.Rt=new A.c("Jugular bulb oxygen saturation (SjvO2) values below _____ suggest cerebral ischemia.","50%")
B.RI=new A.c("Which sedation agent is preferred for its short half-life and rapid emergence, allowing for frequent neurological exams?","Propofol.")
B.a_3=new A.c("What is the normal range for intracranial pressure in a healthy supine adult?","7-15 mmHg (treatment threshold per BTF is >22 mmHg).")
B.TV=new A.c("True or False: Therapeutic hypothermia (32-35 degrees C) is a first-line treatment for ICP elevation.","False (it is a Tier 3/last resort intervention).")
B.iG=s([B.To,B.NO,B.Vu,B.Oe,B.MH,B.ZF,B.Q7,B.WL,B.WV,B.Y_,B.Yz,B.VH,B.a_7,B.P2,B.W2,B.PR,B.MV,B.Xw,B.NM,B.XI,B.P5,B.YA,B.Yw,B.WO,B.Un,B.Qd,B.Yx,B.Ya,B.Na,B.Xt,B.T0,B.US,B.Oa,B.XN,B.Zv,B.a_k,B.Qs,B.Rq,B.Ta,B.Yo,B.QY,B.TQ,B.Vj,B.XZ,B.Zg,B.Ps,B.Po,B.MK,B.Ts,B.QZ,B.PJ,B.RS,B.Vw,B.Sj,B.WT,B.Vr,B.Zi,B.S2,B.QS,B.Oj,B.Oc,B.S7,B.Vg,B.a_Q,B.S_,B.a_C,B.QW,B.O0,B.S0,B.Sx,B.Rt,B.RI,B.a_3,B.TV],t.c)
