B.a9t=s(["Loading doses should be used to overcome the blood-brain barrier.","Start at the lowest effective dose and titrate slowly.","Polypharmacy is encouraged to target multiple neurotransmitter systems simultaneously.","Medications should be titrated rapidly to reach therapeutic levels within 48 hours."],t.s)
B.af9=new A.O("According to the catecholaminergic hypothesis of TBI recovery, which of the following describes the 'Cardinal Rule' for prescribing medications to brain-injured patients?",B.a9t,1,"The 'Start Low, Go Slow' principle accounts for altered metabolism, increased receptor sensitivity, and increased susceptibility to side effects in the injured brain.","pharmacology")
B.a5K=s(["Continue phenytoin for 6 months to prevent late post-traumatic seizures (PTS).","Increase the dose to account for hepatic enzyme induction.","Discontinue phenytoin as it is only indicated for 7 days post-injury.","Switch to phenobarbital for long-term maintenance."],t.s)
B.afM=new A.O("A patient is 14 days post-severe TBI and has not had any documented seizures. According to the Brain Trauma Foundation (BTF) and clinical guidelines, what is the most appropriate management of their phenytoin (Dilantin)?",B.a5K,2,"Prophylaxis is recommended for early PTS (within 7 days) only; continuing it longer causes cognitive impairment and impairs recovery.","pharmacology")
B.a3r=s(["Benzodiazepines increase the duration of chloride channel opening, while barbiturates increase the frequency.","Benzodiazepines increase the frequency of chloride channel opening, while barbiturates increase the duration.","Barbiturates act on GABAB receptors, while benzodiazepines act on GABAA receptors.","Benzodiazepines are direct agonists, whereas barbiturates are positive allosteric modulators."],t.s)
B.ahg=new A.O("Which pharmacological distinction between benzodiazepines and barbiturates is correctly identified?",B.a3r,1,"This specific mechanistic difference at the GABAA receptor is a classic pharmacology distinction tested on board exams.","pharmacology")
B.a9R=s(["Methylphenidate","Amantadine","Bromocriptine","Zolpidem"],t.s)
B.agt=new A.O("Based on the Giacino 2012 NEJM trial, which medication has the strongest evidence for accelerating functional recovery in patients with Disorders of Consciousness (DOC)?",B.a9R,1,"The 2012 trial showed that amantadine (100-200 mg BID) significantly accelerated the pace of functional improvement in patients in vegetative or minimally conscious states.","pharmacology")
B.a6c=s(["It facilitates the presynaptic release of exogenous dopamine.","It acts as a direct agonist at the postsynaptic D2 receptor.","It blocks the reuptake of dopamine (DAT) and norepinephrine (NET).","It inhibits acetylcholinesterase to increase synaptic acetylcholine."],t.s)
B.agT=new A.O("In the management of post-TBI attention deficits and processing speed impairment, what is the primary mechanism of action of the first-line psychostimulant methylphenidate?",B.a6c,2,"Methylphenidate increases catecholamine availability by inhibiting the transporters responsible for their reuptake from the synapse.","pharmacology")
B.a95=s(["Sertraline (SSRI)","Dopaminergic agents (e.g., Methylphenidate or Amantadine)","Trazodone","Valproic acid"],t.s)
B.ah0=new A.O("A patient demonstrates indifference, emotional flatness, and a lack of concern about their condition, but does not report feelings of sadness or guilt. What is the most appropriate first-line pharmacological approach?",B.a95,1,"The symptoms describe apathy (lack of motivation/concern without sadness), which typically responds to dopaminergic stimulation rather than serotonergic agents.","pharmacology")
B.a3C=s(["Atypical antipsychotics like Quetiapine","Benzodiazepines like Lorazepam","Beta-blockers like Propranolol","Typical antipsychotics like Haloperidol"],t.s)
B.agG=new A.O("According to the 2025 UAMS TBI Agitation Guidelines and Cochrane reviews, which medication class is considered the first-line pharmacological treatment for agitation?",B.a3C,2,"Beta-blockers have the best evidence for reducing the intensity of agitation without impeding motor or cognitive recovery.","pharmacology")
B.a6D=s(["Levetiracetam has superior efficacy in preventing late post-traumatic seizures.","Levetiracetam does not require serum level monitoring and has no significant CYP450 interactions.","Levetiracetam acts as a mood stabilizer to reduce irritability.","Levetiracetam is a more potent GABAA receptor modulator."],t.s)
B.aim=new A.O("A clinician is choosing an anticonvulsant for a TBI patient. Which of the following is a primary reason why levetiracetam (Keppra) is increasingly preferred over phenytoin (Dilantin)?",B.a6D,1,"Unlike phenytoin, which is a strong enzyme inducer with a narrow therapeutic index, levetiracetam is renally cleared and easier to manage.","pharmacology")
B.a5R=s(["Gingival hyperplasia","Baclofen withdrawal syndrome","Stevens-Johnson Syndrome (SJS)","Livedo reticularis"],t.s)
B.ahs=new A.O("What is the most critical and potentially fatal complication associated with Intrathecal Baclofen (ITB) therapy in TBI patients?",B.a5R,1,"Sudden cessation of ITB can lead to a life-threatening syndrome characterized by hyperthermia, seizures, and rhabdomyolysis.","pharmacology")
B.a7K=s(["It acts as a selective alpha2 agonist in the brainstem.","It inhibits the release of calcium from the sarcoplasmic reticulum in the muscle.","It is a GABAB agonist that does not cross the blood-brain barrier.","It increases the reuptake of acetylcholine at the neuromuscular junction."],t.s)
B.ahK=new A.O("Which of the following describes the mechanism of dantrolene and explains why it may cause less cognitive sedation than baclofen?",B.a7K,1,"Because dantrolene acts peripherally on the muscle's calcium release rather than centrally in the brain or spinal cord, it has minimal cognitive effects.","pharmacology")
B.a65=s(["Progesterone significantly reduced mortality by 17%.","The trials were terminated early due to excessive thromboembolic events.","Both trials failed to show any significant benefit over placebo.","Progesterone is now the standard of care for severe TBI neuroprotection."],t.s)
B.agL=new A.O("Regarding the 2014 Phase III trials (PROTECT III and SyNAPSe) for progesterone in acute TBI, what was the clinical outcome?",B.a65,2,"Despite strong preclinical data and positive Phase II results, the Phase III trials showed no functional improvement for progesterone.","pharmacology")
B.a7z=s(["Diphenhydramine (Benadryl)","Trazodone","Zolpidem (Ambien)","Lorazepam (Ativan)"],t.s)
B.afw=new A.O("Which medication is generally considered the 'first choice' for treating insomnia in TBI patients due to its non-habit-forming nature and lack of cognitive impairment?",B.a7z,1,"Trazodone is preferred for TBI-related sleep disturbances because it is effective and lacks the cognitive risks of benzodiazepines or anticholinergics.","pharmacology")
B.a97=s([B.af9,B.afM,B.ahg,B.agt,B.agT,B.ah0,B.agG,B.aim,B.ahs,B.ahK,B.agL,B.afw],t.e)
B.dR=new A.ol(0,"idle")
B.AT=new A.ol(1,"loading")
B.j4=new A.ol(2,"buffering")
B.ml=new A.ol(3,"ready")
B.AU=new A.ol(4,"completed")
