B.MM=new A.c("Posttraumatic agitation is considered a specific subtype of which neurocognitive condition?","Delirium")
B.UF=new A.c("During which specific period of recovery does posttraumatic agitation occur?","Posttraumatic amnesia (PTA)")
B.Tb=new A.c("Which Rancho Los Amigos Level corresponds to the 'Confused-Agitated' state?","Level IV")
B.SU=new A.c("What is the estimated incidence of posttraumatic agitation among TBI patients in acute inpatient rehabilitation?","Approximately 33%")
B.VR=new A.c("What is the typical duration range for a self-limited episode of posttraumatic agitation?","1 to 14 days")
B.V4=new A.c("Most cases of posttraumatic agitation resolve within what time frame?","1 to 2 months")
B.Xy=new A.c("Agitation is most commonly associated with lesions in which brain region?","Frontotemporal")
B.S3=new A.c("What capacity for learning do patients possess during the agitated phase of PTA?","None")
B.Vn=new A.c("Why should physical restraints be minimized in agitated TBI patients?","They can increase agitation.")
B.RE=new A.c("According to the Clinical Pearl in Cuccurullo, what must a clinician do instead of using the generic word 'agitation'?","Identify the specific problem behavior (e.g., aggression, akathisia).")
B.O6=new A.c("Who developed the Agitated Behavior Scale (ABS) in 1989?","Corrigan")
B.a_c=new A.c("How many behavioral items are included in the Agitated Behavior Scale (ABS)?","14 items")
B.Z4=new A.c("What is the scoring range for a single item on the Agitated Behavior Scale (ABS)?","1 (absent) to 4 (present to an extreme degree)")
B.UY=new A.c("What is the total possible score range for the Agitated Behavior Scale (ABS)?","14 to 56")
B.NT=new A.c("What is the clinically significant cutoff score on the ABS indicating agitation?","A score > 21")
B.V6=new A.c("In the ABS scoring thresholds, what severity is represented by a score of 22-28?","Mild agitation")
B.Uq=new A.c("In the ABS scoring thresholds, what severity is represented by a score of 29-35?","Moderate agitation")
B.RP=new A.c("An ABS score greater than 35 indicates what severity level of agitation?","Severe")
B.Wd=new A.c("The 2023 factor analysis of the ABS identified which factor as being related to motor movements and pacing?","Factor 1: Restlessness")
B.NI=new A.c("The 2023 factor analysis of the ABS identified which factor as being related to violence, anger, and mood changes?","Factor 2: Aggression/Lability")
B.T8=new A.c("Which agitation assessment tool uses 47 characteristics scored by frequency?","Overt Aggression Scale (OAS)")
B.Zd=new A.c("The Behavioral Assessment Screening Tool (BAST) is primarily designed for which TBI population?","Chronic brain injury")
B.Z8=new A.c("What is the single most important principle/Step 1 in the management of agitation?","Rule out medical causes first.")
B.Ok=new A.c("What is considered the most common treatable medical cause of agitation in TBI?","Pain")
B.Sd=new A.c("If agitation is new, worsening, or atypical, which diagnostic test should be obtained to rule out nonconvulsive status epilepticus?","Electroencephalogram (EEG)")
B.Om=new A.c("Which two common gastrointestinal/genitourinary triggers for agitation are frequently overlooked?","Constipation and urinary retention")
B.Tr=new A.c("In clinical board exams, what is always the correct first step for managing agitation?","Environmental modification")
B.RK=new A.c("What type of specialized bed is recommended to protect agitated patients from self-harm while allowing movement?",u.C)
B.ZG=new A.c("What is the recommended staffing ratio for observing a severely agitated patient to ensure safety without restraints?","1:1 sitter")
B.PZ=new A.c("Why is it recommended to have only one person speak to an agitated patient at a time?","To reduce cognitive confusion.")
B.RB=new A.c("The 'A-B-C' model in behavior management plans stands for what three components?","Antecedents, Behaviors, and Consequences")
B.WD=new A.c("What is the first-line pharmacological agent for posttraumatic agitation based on Cochrane evidence?","Propranolol")
B.R_=new A.c("What is the typical starting dose range for Propranolol in agitation management?","20-60 mg TID-QID")
B.Sa=new A.c("Under what heart rate condition should a clinician hold a dose of Propranolol?","Heart rate < 60 bpm")
B.Ul=new A.c("Under what blood pressure condition should a clinician hold a dose of Propranolol?","Systolic blood pressure < 90 mmHg")
B.Q8=new A.c("Which second-line medication provides a dual benefit of reducing agitation and promoting functional recovery?","Amantadine")
B.Pj=new A.c("What is the standard dosing and timing for Amantadine in TBI recovery?","100 mg BID, with the second dose by noon.")
B.ZD=new A.c("Why is the second dose of Amantadine typically given by noon?","To avoid insomnia.")
B.YW=new A.c("Which third-line medication is preferred if the patient has a high risk of seizures along with agitation?","Valproic acid")
B.QT=new A.c("Why is Valproic acid often preferred over Levetiracetam in agitated patients?","Levetiracetam can cause or worsen agitation.")
B.OC=new A.c("Which medication is prioritized when sleep disturbance is a primary contributor to agitation?","Trazodone")
B.WX=new A.c("Why is Haloperidol (Haldol) generally avoided in TBI patients?","It hinders motor and cognitive recovery and prolongs PTA.")
B.Oy=new A.c("What is the primary concern regarding the use of benzodiazepines in patients emerging from PTA?","Amnestic effects increase confusion and can cause paradoxical agitation.")
B.a_J=new A.c("Which atypical antipsychotic is suggested as a practical PRN alternative for acute agitation over Haloperidol?","Olanzapine")
B.YO=new A.c("Which emerging agent is an alpha-2 adrenergic receptor agonist used for acute ICU agitation?","Dexmedetomidine")
B.UE=new A.c("What is the major limitation of the current formulation of Dexmedetomidine (Precedex)?","It is an IV formulation, limiting use to the ICU.")
B.Nf=new A.c("Paroxysmal Sympathetic Hyperactivity (PSH) is characterized by episodic discharge of which system?","Sympathetic nervous system")
B.Q5=new A.c("How many of the six clinical features are required to diagnose PSH?","4 out of 6")
B.Yg=new A.c("What is the heart rate threshold used in PSH diagnostic criteria?","Tachycardia > 120-130 bpm")
B.Si=new A.c("What temperature threshold defines fever in PSH diagnostic criteria?","> 38.5degreesC (101.3degreesF)")
B.Rj=new A.c("Which PSH clinical feature involves profuse, drenching sweat?","Diaphoresis")
B.Wm=new A.c("What is the first-line treatment for acute, breakthrough episodes of PSH?","Morphine (or other opioids)")
B.Uc=new A.c("Which medication acts at the muscle level to treat rigidity or posturing in PSH?","Dantrolene")
B.Qp=new A.c("Which treatment is reserved for PSH that is refractory to all oral medications?","Intrathecal Baclofen (ITB) pump")
B.Wh=new A.c("In terms of timing, when does PSH typically occur compared to posttraumatic agitation?","PSH occurs in the first 2 weeks; agitation occurs in weeks 2-8 (PTA phase).")
B.Y7=new A.c("Pseudobulbar Affect (PBA) is characterized by involuntary episodes of what two behaviors?","Laughing or crying")
B.Wg=new A.c("What is the primary screening tool for Pseudobulbar Affect (PBA)?","Center for Neurologic Study-Lability Scale (CNS-LS)")
B.UH=new A.c("What score on the CNS-LS suggests the presence of Pseudobulbar Affect (PBA)?","A score >=13")
B.UW=new A.c("Which medication is FDA-approved specifically for the treatment of PBA?","Nuedexta (Dextromethorphan/Quinidine)")
B.SG=new A.c("What is the role of Quinidine in the combination drug Nuedexta?","It inhibits CYP2D6 to increase the bioavailability of Dextromethorphan.")
B.Qk=new A.c("What is the estimated prevalence of depression beyond 12 months post-TBI?","Approximately 33%")
B.VX=new A.c("Which screening tool is standard for assessing depression severity in TBI patients?","PHQ-9")
B.Ng=new A.c("A score of 10 on the GAD-7 screening tool indicates what level of anxiety?","Moderate anxiety")
B.Wu=new A.c("What percentage of TBI patients requiring inpatient rehab are estimated to have a pre-injury history of substance use disorder (SUD)?","Up to 60%")
B.UJ=new A.c("In the BID dosing of Amantadine, when should the second dose be administered?","By noon")
B.Nj=new A.c("According to the Cochrane Review, which class of drugs has the best evidence for managing agitation and aggression?","Beta-blockers")
B.Z2=new A.c("Which ABS item involves repetitive motor or verbal behaviors?","Item 10")
B.T1=new A.c("What is the name of the tool used to determine the diagnosis likelihood of PSH?","Diagnosis Likelihood Tool (DLT)")
B.PH=new A.c("What is the recommended first-line pharmacological class for posttraumatic irritability?",u.F)
B.PY=new A.c("Which medication is used specifically for aggressive hypersexual behavior by lowering testosterone?","Medroxyprogesterone acetate")
B.W1=new A.c("Which drug interaction must be monitored when using Valproic acid for agitation?","Lamotrigine (or Carbamazepine/Phenytoin)")
B.VQ=new A.c("In the context of TBI and SUD, which usually occurs first: the TBI or the opioid use?","TBI usually precedes opioid use.")
B.RT=new A.c("What is the score range for a 'probable' diagnosis of PSH using the PSH-AM?","A score >= 17 (8-16 = possible; <8 = unlikely)")
B.TD=new A.c("Which factor in the ABS 2023 update includes crying and laughter?","Factor 2: Aggression/Lability")
B.iH=s([B.MM,B.UF,B.Tb,B.SU,B.VR,B.V4,B.Xy,B.S3,B.Vn,B.RE,B.O6,B.a_c,B.Z4,B.UY,B.NT,B.V6,B.Uq,B.RP,B.Wd,B.NI,B.T8,B.Zd,B.Z8,B.Ok,B.Sd,B.Om,B.Tr,B.RK,B.ZG,B.PZ,B.RB,B.WD,B.R_,B.Sa,B.Ul,B.Q8,B.Pj,B.ZD,B.YW,B.QT,B.OC,B.WX,B.Oy,B.a_J,B.YO,B.UE,B.Nf,B.Q5,B.Yg,B.Si,B.Rj,B.Wm,B.Uc,B.Qp,B.Wh,B.Y7,B.Wg,B.UH,B.UW,B.SG,B.Qk,B.VX,B.Ng,B.Wu,B.UJ,B.Nj,B.Z2,B.T1,B.PH,B.PY,B.W1,B.VQ,B.RT,B.TD],t.c)
B.V1=new A.c("What is the leading cause of traumatic brain injury (TBI) in children aged 0-14 years?","Falls.")
B.QE=new A.c("Which age group has the highest rate of emergency department visits for TBI of any demographic?","Children aged 0-4 years.")
B.X_=new A.c("What is the leading cause of TBI in adolescents aged 15-19 years?","Motor vehicle crashes.")
B.Uf=new A.c("TBI is the leading cause of death in children over what age?","1 year of age.")
B.NZ=new A.c('What is the preferred clinical term for TBI caused by infant shaking or impact, replacing "shaken baby syndrome"?',"Abusive head trauma (AHT).")
B.OO=new A.c("At what age range is the peak incidence of abusive head trauma observed?","2-4 months of age.")
B.Sv=new A.c('Which three findings constitute the "classic triad" of abusive head trauma?',"Subdural hematomas, retinal hemorrhages, and encephalopathy.")
B.PF=new A.c("What is the most specific physical finding for abusive head trauma, occurring in ~ 85% of cases?","Retinal hemorrhages.")
B.TE=new A.c("Retinal hemorrhages indicative of AHT typically extend to the _____ of the eye.","Periphery (beyond the posterior pole).")
B.NV=new A.c("Which diagnostic gold standard provides a 130-degree field of view for imaging retinal hemorrhages in infants?","RetCam digital wide-field fundus photography (DWFFP).")
B.MG=new A.c("Which MRI sequence is specifically used to detect cortical venous injury and retinal hemorrhages noninvasively?","Susceptibility-weighted imaging (SWI).")
B.Ub=new A.c("The Pittsburgh Infant Brain Injury Score (PIBIS) targets head CT use; what score indicates a high likelihood of a positive result?","A score of 2.")
B.Za=new A.c("According to the ACR, what is the initial screening tool for suspected non-accidental trauma in children < 24 months?","Skeletal survey.")
B.MD=new A.c("What is the primary purpose of the Pediatric Emergency Care Applied Research Network (PECARN) decision rules?","To identify children at very low risk of clinically important TBI who do not require a CT scan.")
B.Zy=new A.c("In the PECARN algorithm for children < 2 years, what are the three criteria for a recommended CT scan?","GCS < 15, palpable skull fracture, or altered mental status.")
B.TZ=new A.c("In the PECARN algorithm for children >=2 years, what are the three criteria for a recommended CT scan?","GCS < 15, altered mental status, or signs of basilar skull fracture.")
B.Rw=new A.c("For children >=2 years with no PECARN risk factors, what is the negative predictive value (NPV) for clinically important TBI?","> 99.9%.")
B.Vl=new A.c("How is the verbal component of the Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) modified for a cooing or babbling preverbal child?","It is assigned a maximum score of 5.")
B.P7=new A.c("In the pediatric GCS, what verbal score is assigned to a child who cries persistently to pain?","3.")
B.Nh=new A.c("In the pediatric GCS, what motor score is assigned for spontaneous purposeful movements?","6.")
B.QQ=new A.c("Why is the pediatric GCS often less accurate in children < 9-18 months for motor scoring?","Children in this age group cannot reliably localize noxious stimuli.")
B.T5=new A.c("Which assessment tool is used specifically to evaluate orientation and attention in children < 15 years old?","Children's Orientation and Attention Test (COAT).")
B.UR=new A.c("Which tool is validated for assessing disorders of consciousness in children aged 1-5 years?","Coma Recovery Scale for Pediatrics (CRS-P).")
B.W5=new A.c("What is the name of the debunked principle that suggested younger brains are more resilient and recover better from injury?","The Kennard principle.")
B.U0=new A.c("What phenomenon describes TBI deficits that only become apparent as a child's higher cognitive demands increase during development?",'"Growing into deficits."')
B.Zl=new A.c("Why are unmyelinated axons in the developing brain more susceptible to shearing forces (DAI)?","Myelination is incomplete until the mid-20s, leaving younger axons more vulnerable.")
B.Ye=new A.c("Which pediatric age group shows the worst long-term cognitive outcomes following a TBI?","Children injured before age 5.")
B.O1=new A.c("How does the risk of early posttraumatic seizures in children compare to adults?","Children have a higher risk of early posttraumatic seizures.")
B.Qj=new A.c("What type of seizure occurring within seconds of injury is more common in children and generally considered benign?","Impact seizures.")
B.Qm=new A.c("Which vascular complication is the pediatric brain more prone to following TBI than the adult brain?","Diffuse cerebral swelling (edema).")
B.XB=new A.c("Following a moderate-to-severe pediatric TBI, which endocrine axis should be screened due to potential growth velocity changes?","The growth hormone axis (hypopituitarism).")
B.MN=new A.c("According to 2025 CDC guidelines, how soon can most children return to school after a concussion?","Within 1-2 days.")
B.PB=new A.c("What formal support plan is recommended when a student's concussion symptoms persist beyond 4 weeks?","Section 504 Plan.")
B.Q3=new A.c("The 2023 Amsterdam Consensus Statement defines the pediatric recovery timeline for concussion as up to _____.","4 weeks.")
B.SI=new A.c("In youth concussion management, what is the current recommendation regarding strict rest in the first 48 hours?","Strict rest is not beneficial; early return to light physical activity is recommended.")
B.Uj=new A.c("What is the leading cause of TBI in adults aged >=75 years?","Falls (> 80% of cases).")
B.Y3=new A.c("How does age-related brain atrophy affect the volume of the subdural space?","It increases the subdural space from 6% to 11% of intracranial volume.")
B.Z6=new A.c("What is the most common traumatic intracranial lesion found in the elderly population?","Subdural hematoma (SDH).")
B.WR=new A.c("Which vascular structures are stretched by brain atrophy, making them vulnerable to tearing in geriatric TBI?","Bridging veins.")
B.NR=new A.c('Why is chronic SDH often referred to as the "Great Imitator" in geriatric patients?',"Its symptoms, like cognitive decline and gait instability, frequently mimic dementia or NPH.")
B.Nc=new A.c("What emerging procedure involves blocking a specific artery to reduce the recurrence of chronic subdural hematomas?","Middle Meningeal Artery (MMA) embolization.")
B.QG=new A.c("According to the STEM trial (2024), MMA embolization reduced chronic SDH recurrence events from 36% to _____.","16%.")
B.Yy=new A.c("What is the typical recurrence rate range for chronic subdural hematomas in elderly patients?","9-33%.")
B.PD=new A.c("What is the clinical recommendation for an elderly patient on anticoagulation who sustains a minor head injury without LOC?","Perform a CT scan regardless of the lack of symptoms.")
B.ZU=new A.c("Which medication is the specific reversal agent for the direct thrombin inhibitor Dabigatran?","Idarucizumab (Praxbind).")
B.On=new A.c("What is the specific reversal agent for Factor Xa inhibitors like Rivaroxaban and Apixaban?","Andexanet alfa (Andexxa).")
B.QM=new A.c("How does the risk of traumatic intracranial hemorrhage (ICH) with DOACs compare to Warfarin?","DOACs are associated with a reduced risk of traumatic ICH.")
B.Pi=new A.c("Delayed hemorrhage in anticoagulated geriatric patients can occur up to _____ hours after the initial injury.","24-72 hours.")
B.Ro=new A.c("Which bedside tool, scoring from 1 to 9, is an independent predictor of outcomes in geriatric TBI?","Clinical Frailty Scale (CFS).")
B.SX=new A.c("What is the approximate 6-month mortality rate for a geriatric TBI patient with a Clinical Frailty Scale score >=4?","87%.")
B.UO=new A.c("Which class of medications should be aggressively avoided in elderly TBI patients due to delirium risk?","Anticholinergics (e.g., diphenhydramine, oxybutynin).")
B.Zq=new A.c("Why are benzodiazepines generally avoided in geriatric TBI management?","They increase falls risk and can cause paradoxical agitation or cognitive worsening.")
B.Us=new A.c("Which antidepressant class is preferred for geriatric TBI, provided the patient is monitored for SIADH?","Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs).")
B.PV=new A.c("What is the average reduction in life expectancy for an elderly patient following a TBI?","6-9 years.")
B.Xv=new A.c("How much higher is the in-hospital mortality rate for geriatric TBI compared to younger adults with comparable injury severity?","2-3 times higher.")
B.Qt=new A.c("What is the strongest genetic risk factor for poor outcomes following a TBI?","ApoE4 allele.")
B.NC=new A.c("Carrying at least one ApoE4 allele is associated with what recovery pattern in TBI?","Longer coma, slower cognitive recovery, and higher mortality.")
B.OY=new A.c("A homozygous carrier of the ApoE4 allele has a _____ increased risk of Alzheimer's Disease.","12-15x.")
B.a_1=new A.c("What percentage of the general population carries at least one ApoE4 allele?","15-25%.")
B.UT=new A.c("Under the PECARN rules, what is the recommended action if a child < 2 years has a non-frontal scalp hematoma?","Observation vs. CT scan.")
B.Vs=new A.c("Which specific MRI sequence is noted for improved identification of retinal hemorrhages in AHT cases?","Balanced steady-state field precession (bSSFP).")
B.Sg=new A.c('In the context of NAT screening, what does the presence of "metaphyseal bucket handle fractures" suggest?',"Abusive head trauma/Non-accidental trauma.")
B.Ri=new A.c("What is the primary criteria for inpatient rehabilitation eligibility in geriatric TBI?","The patient must be medically stable and tolerate 3 hours of therapy across 2+ disciplines.")
B.XE=new A.c("Cervicovestibular rehabilitation is specifically recommended for adolescents with dizziness or headache persisting beyond how many days?","10 days.")
B.a_4=new A.c("What is the specific motor response for a pGCS score of 1?","None.")
B.Rp=new A.c("Which age group of children uses the SCAT6 Child Version for concussion assessment?","Ages 8-12 (narrowed from 5-12 in Child-SCAT5).")
B.SN=new A.c("How does the risk of post-traumatic epilepsy in children compare to adults for similar injury severity?","The risk is lower in children.")
B.X6=new A.c('What is the primary risk of using Baclofen in elderly TBI patients, requiring a "start low, go slow" approach?',"High risk of sedation and cognitive impairment.")
B.SJ=new A.c("A suspected AHT case with a history that is inconsistent with the child's developmental stage is considered a _____.","Red flag.")
B.XQ=new A.c("What is the reported mortality range for survivors of abusive head trauma?","15-25%.")
B.YY=new A.c("Which tool provides cross-sectional retinal imaging to distinguish abusive from non-abusive trauma?","Optical coherence tomography (OCT).")
B.Xs=new A.c("Which PECARN age group includes a history of vomiting as a criterion for observation vs. CT?","Children >=2 years.")
B.Ua=new A.c("A child who only moans or grunts to pain would receive what pGCS verbal score?","2.")
B.OV=new A.c("The increase in geriatric TBI incidence is largely attributed to what two factors?","Increased life expectancy and more active lifestyles.")
B.Xh=new A.c("What is the mortality rate for TBI in patients aged 65-70 with moderate-to-severe injuries?","~ 71%.")
B.Os=new A.c("Which type of bedside craniostomy is used for chronic SDH to avoid general anesthesia in frail patients?","Twist-drill craniostomy (TDC).")
B.NE=new A.c("What is the risk of post-TBI depression in the geriatric population?","25-50%.")
B.XL=new A.c('For a preverbal child, what pGCS verbal score is given for an "irritable, cries but consolable" response?',"4.")
B.YE=new A.c("The Amsterdam 2023 consensus recommends cervicovestibular rehab for adolescents if neck pain persists for more than _____.","10 days.")
B.ZZ=new A.c("In AHT cases, which rib fractures are considered highly suspicious for non-accidental trauma?","Posterior rib fractures.")
