B.VI=new A.c("Posttraumatic seizures occurring within the first 24 hours after injury are classified as _____ PTS.","Immediate")
B.a_g=new A.c("What is the specific time window for 'Early' posttraumatic seizures?","24 hours to 7 days post-injury")
B.Qn=new A.c("Posttraumatic seizures occurring more than 7 days after injury are classified as _____ PTS.","Late")
B.Ys=new A.c("What clinical condition is defined by the occurrence of recurrent late posttraumatic seizures?","Posttraumatic epilepsy (PTE)")
B.Ti=new A.c("According to the Temkin trial (1990), for how many days should AED prophylaxis be administered after TBI?","7 days")
B.OB=new A.c("Why is AED prophylaxis for posttraumatic seizures discontinued after the first week?","Evidence shows it reduces early seizures but does not prevent late seizures.")
B.XU=new A.c("Which TBI severity type carries the highest risk (33-50%) for developing posttraumatic epilepsy?","Penetrating TBI")
B.Qf=new A.c("How does the risk of late PTS change if a patient experiences an early PTS within the first week?","The risk of developing late PTS increases to 25%.")
B.Wz=new A.c("Which specific cortical contusion locations are most strongly associated with an elevated risk of late PTS?","Temporal and frontal lobes")
B.SE=new A.c("Comparing phenytoin and levetiracetam, which medication requires routine drug level monitoring?","Phenytoin")
B.U9=new A.c("What is a significant cognitive disadvantage of using phenytoin for seizure prophylaxis?","It impairs attention and processing speed.")
B.PO=new A.c("Which second-generation AED is increasingly preferred in TBI due to its minimal cognitive side effects and lack of required drug monitoring?","Levetiracetam")
B.Q6=new A.c("What is the probability of seizure recurrence within 2 years after the first episode of late PTS?","86%")
B.Sr=new A.c("What percentage of patients with refractory posttraumatic epilepsy are found to have psychogenic non-epileptic seizures (PNES)?","20-30%")
B.RD=new A.c("Passive ventricular dilation resulting from brain atrophy rather than impaired CSF flow is called _____.","Ventriculomegaly ex vacuo")
B.Vp=new A.c("True posttraumatic hydrocephalus (PTH) occurs in approximately what percentage of severe TBI cases?","3.9-8%")
B.XX=new A.c("How does a decompressive craniectomy affect the risk of developing posttraumatic hydrocephalus?","It increases the rate to approximately 27%.")
B.Pa=new A.c("In which type of hydrocephalus is the obstruction located at the arachnoid granulations?","Communicating hydrocephalus")
B.Uu=new A.c("What are the three components of the Hakim-Adams syndrome triad?","Gait disturbance, urinary incontinence, and dementia")
B.SV=new A.c("Which symptom of the NPH triad is typically the first to appear and the most responsive to shunting?","Gait disturbance")
B.Xo=new A.c("What radiographic finding helps distinguish true PTH from atrophy on a CT scan?","Periventricular lucency")
B.Ud=new A.c("The Evans Index threshold used to support a diagnosis of hydrocephalus is _____.",">0.30")
B.Z9=new A.c("What complication can occur from over-drainage of a ventriculoperitoneal shunt?","Subdural hematoma")
B.NL=new A.c("What is the definition of heterotopic ossification (HO)?","Formation of mature lamellar bone in soft tissues surrounding joints")
B.Vt=new A.c("What is the most common anatomical site for clinically significant HO in the TBI population?","Hips")
B.Sp=new A.c("HO in TBI patients typically reaches its peak onset at how many months post-injury?","2 months")
B.Ny=new A.c("Which clinical symptom is the most sensitive early indicator for detecting HO?","Decreased range of motion")
B.Wk=new A.c("Which diagnostic test is considered the gold standard for the early detection of HO?","Triple-phase bone scan")
B.Xz=new A.c("How long before X-ray changes can a triple-phase bone scan detect active HO?","2-4 weeks")
B.V7=new A.c("Which serum marker is monitored to assess the maturation of heterotopic bone?","Alkaline phosphatase")
B.ZW=new A.c("What is the gold standard NSAID used for the prevention of HO?","Indomethacin")
B.Xg=new A.c("According to Garland timing, how long should surgical excision of HO be delayed in TBI patients?","1.5 years")
B.NF=new A.c("What must occur on a triple-phase bone scan to indicate HO bone maturity?","Phases 1 and 2 must normalize (cooling).")
B.YN=new A.c("What is the leading cause of preventable death in rehabilitation patients?","Pulmonary embolism (PE)")
B.QC=new A.c("Virchow's triad, which describes the factors contributing to VTE, consists of venous stasis, vessel wall damage, and _____.","Hypercoagulable state")
B.YB=new A.c("What is the preferred LMWH prophylactic dose for VTE in TBI patients?","Enoxaparin 30 mg SC every 12 hours")
B.YH=new A.c("What is the target range for anti-factor Xa levels when monitoring enoxaparin prophylaxis?","0.2-0.4 IU/mL")
B.XD=new A.c("Which diagnostic test is 95% sensitive for detecting symptomatic proximal DVT?","Doppler ultrasonography")
B.a_t=new A.c("Which specialized test provides real-time, whole-blood assessment of TBI-induced coagulopathy?","Viscoelastic testing (TEG or ROTEM)")
B.a_8=new A.c("According to the CRASH-3 trial, which TBI subgroup benefits from tranexamic acid (TXA) within 3 hours of injury?","Mild-to-moderate TBI (GCS 9-15)")
B.NW=new A.c("What is the ranking of the three most commonly injured cranial nerves in TBI?","CN I (Olfactory) > CN VII (Facial) > CN VIII (Vestibulocochlear)")
B.TU=new A.c("What is the primary mechanism of injury for the olfactory nerve (CN I) during head trauma?","Shearing of filaments at the cribriform plate")
B.W_=new A.c("Why should ammonia not be used when testing for CN I function?","It stimulates the trigeminal nerve (CN V), potentially creating a false-negative result.")
B.Su=new A.c("What is the most evidence-based rehabilitation approach for olfactory nerve injury?","Olfactory training (systematic sniffing)")
B.PC=new A.c("In CN VII (Facial) injuries, what does an immediate onset of palsy typically suggest regarding the nerve?","Nerve transection")
B.a_i=new A.c("A longitudinal temporal bone fracture is most likely to cause which type of hearing loss?","Conductive hearing loss")
B.WA=new A.c("Which oculomotor nerve is most frequently injured in TBI due to its long intracranial course and dorsal exit?","CN IV (Trochlear)")
B.TW=new A.c("What compensatory posture is common in patients with a CN IV (Trochlear) palsy?","Head tilt away from the affected side")
B.Nt=new A.c("Why is a CN VI (Abducens) palsy considered a 'false localizing sign' in TBI?","It can be caused by elevated intracranial pressure rather than a focal lesion.")
B.Rc=new A.c("What is the consensus term for transient increases in sympathetic and motor activity after severe TBI?","Paroxysmal sympathetic hyperactivity (PSH)")
B.a_x=new A.c("The PSH Assessment Measure (PSH-AM) consists of the Clinical Feature Scale and the _____.","Diagnosis Likelihood Tool (DLT)")
B.ZV=new A.c("List four of the six cardinal features scored in the PSH Clinical Feature Scale.","Heart rate, blood pressure, respiratory rate, temperature, sweating, or posturing")
B.ZT=new A.c("Which nonselective beta-blocker has the best Cochrane evidence for recurrence prevention in PSH?","Propranolol")
B.S9=new A.c("Which medication is typically considered Tier 1 for managing acute episodes of sympathetic storming?","Morphine or fentanyl")
B.Qg=new A.c("What is the most common neuroendocrine disorder seen following a traumatic brain injury?","SIADH")
B.QH=new A.c("What is the clinical volume status of a patient with SIADH?","Euvolemic")
B.NP=new A.c("What is the primary treatment for hyponatremia caused by SIADH?","Fluid restriction")
B.Zr=new A.c("What is the clinical volume status of a patient with Cerebral Salt Wasting (CSW)?","Hypovolemic")
B.a_6=new A.c("Treating Cerebral Salt Wasting with fluid restriction is dangerous because it can jeopardize _____.","Cerebral perfusion")
B.Xf=new A.c("Hyponatremia correction should not exceed _____ mEq/L per 24 hours to avoid osmotic demyelination.","10 mEq/L")
B.Nq=new A.c("Which disorder is characterized by hypernatremia and low urine osmolality following injury to the pituitary stalk?","Diabetes Insipidus (DI)")
B.UL=new A.c("What is the first-line pharmacologic treatment for Central Diabetes Insipidus?","Desmopressin (DDAVP)")
B.Ow=new A.c("Which hormone deficiency is the most common pituitary deficit seen 3 months after TBI?","Growth hormone (GH) deficiency")
B.YC=new A.c("What laboratory test is used to screen for ACTH deficiency in the acute phase of TBI?","Morning cortisol")
B.R3=new A.c("What is the target temperature range for 'controlled normothermia' in severe TBI management?","36.0-37.5 degrees C")
B.a_B=new A.c("Why is it critical to manage shivering during the maintenance of normothermia?","Shivering increases metabolic rate and metabolic demand in the brain.")
B.Ui=new A.c("How does the incidence of Ventilator-Associated Pneumonia (VAP) in TBI patients compare to the general ICU population?","It is nearly double the general ICU rate.")
B.U6=new A.c("What is the recommended head-of-bed elevation to prevent VAP in severe TBI patients?","30-45 degrees")
B.PK=new A.c("The 2025 review term 'NODS' stands for _____.","Neurogenic Organ Dysfunction Syndrome")
B.NG=new A.c("TBI patients have an elevated long-term risk of which two major cardiovascular events compared to controls?","Stroke and myocardial infarction")
B.Ra=new A.c("What gastrointestinal condition is common in moderate-to-severe TBI due to vagal dysfunction?","Gastroparesis")
B.WE=new A.c("Which medication is the drug of choice for partial seizures in the TBI population?","Carbamazepine")
B.a_G=new A.c("What is the preferred medication for treating post-TBI hypertension associated with sympathetic hyperactivity?","Propranolol")
B.XJ=new A.c("What is the characteristic pattern of a disinhibited neurogenic bladder in TBI?","Reduced bladder volume with complete emptying via uninhibited contractions.")
B.a_n=new A.c("What percentage of baseline caloric needs do TBI patients typically require due to hypermetabolism?","100-140%")
B.a_z=new A.c("Why should metoclopramide be avoided for GERD management in TBI patients?","It can cause sedation and extrapyramidal symptoms.")
B.U8=new A.c("A transverse temporal bone fracture is more likely to cause which type of hearing loss?","Sensorineural hearing loss")
B.TM=new A.c("Which cranial nerve palsy causes difficulty reading and descending stairs?","CN IV (Trochlear)")
B.VJ=new A.c("What is the diagnostic implication of a 'cooling' triple-phase bone scan in HO management?","It indicates that the heterotopic bone is mature and safe for surgical excision.")
B.a_O=new A.c("What common clinical plateau or decline in TBI rehabilitation may be the first sign of PTH?","Deterioration in gait or cognition")
