B.a3n=s(["5-10%","15-20%","31-39%","75-80%"],t.s)
B.ahu=new A.O("According to research on Intimate Partner Violence (IPV) and TBI, what percentage of IPV cases are estimated to involve a traumatic brain injury?",B.a3n,2,"Nearly one-third to nearly forty percent of IPV cases involve a TBI, highlighting it as a major underreported cause.","tbi-fundamentals")
B.a8s=s(["Blood and Interstitial Fluid","Blood and Cerebrospinal Fluid (CSF)","Cerebrospinal Fluid and Lymphatic Fluid","Gray Matter and White Matter"],t.s)
B.ag1=new A.O("The Monro-Kellie Doctrine describes the pressure-volume relationship within the skull. If the brain accounts for approximately 80% of the intracranial volume, what are the other two primary components that make up the remaining 20%?",B.a8s,1,"The skull contains brain (80%), blood (10%), and CSF (10%). According to the Monro-Kellie Doctrine, an increase in one component must be compensated by a decrease in another.","tbi-fundamentals")
B.a5s=s(["Injury resulting from the overpressure wave itself","Injury resulting from projectiles or debris energized by the blast","Injury resulting from the body being physically displaced or propelled","Injury resulting from burns or inhalation of toxic gases"],t.s)
B.ag3=new A.O("Which of the following describes the 'secondary' mechanism of injury in a blast-related TBI according to the '1-2-3-4' mnemonic?",B.a5s,1,"Primary = blast wave/overpressure, Secondary = projectiles/debris, Tertiary = body displacement/propulsion, Quaternary = burns/inhalation/toxic exposure.","tbi-fundamentals")
B.a3q=s(["The FDA approved the first disease-modifying drug for TBI","CMS added TBI to its list of chronic conditions","The CDC mandated universal helmet use for all sports","The PACT Act was repealed in favor of a TBI-specific bill"],t.s)
B.afv=new A.O("TBI is increasingly recognized as a chronic disease. Which significant policy change occurred in June 2024 to reflect this shift in management?",B.a3q,1,"CMS adding TBI to its chronic conditions list allows for the development of Special Needs Plans.","tbi-fundamentals")
B.aa2=s(["10-25%","30-50%","63-96%","Over 200%"],t.s)
B.ai6=new A.O("Recent longitudinal data from TBIMS indicates that TBI of any severity significantly increases the risk of neurodegeneration. By what range is the risk of all-cause dementia increased following a TBI?",B.aa2,2,"Research shows a nearly 2-fold increase in dementia risk (63-96%) for individuals with a history of TBI.","tbi-fundamentals")
B.aae=s(["Positive tau-PET scan imaging","History of a single severe TBI with GCS less than 8","Cognitive impairment in memory/executive function or neurobehavioral dysregulation","Detection of p-tau217 in the cerebrospinal fluid"],t.s)
